\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Jordan Lyonnais
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 BofA Securities, Research Division
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 I wanted to ask on Autos. How should we think about the growth going into next year and until the BMW -- or sorry, the two 2027 contracts start up with your lines that are retiring?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Clifton Pemble
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 President, CEO & Director
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Yes. So going into next year, as we've communicated, we've been in the peak adoption of the BMW program for a while now, actually have anniversaried that. And as some of these end-of-life programs wind down, 2026 could experience some revenue pressure because of those natural dynamics. We expect the new program to come online towards the back half of 2026. And so we're on track for that, and we continue to make progress in delivering that.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Jordan Lyonnais
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 BofA Securities, Research Division
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Got it. And on Aviation too, was there any greater driver of the growth that you saw between OEM and aftermarket that you could give more detail on?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Clifton Pemble
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 President, CEO & Director
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Yes. I think they're both very comparable, both very strong for different reasons. The backlog in OEM, as you know, is very long. And so aircraft makers are building to that backlog, and we're benefiting from that. And in the aftermarket, the consumer behavior was resilient and people buying and equipping their aircraft. And so the trends are very positive there.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Operator
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Your next question comes from the line of David MacGregor with Longbow Research.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Joseph Nolan
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 Longbow Research LLC
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 This is Joe Nolan on for David. The Fitness business saw another great quarter. Just if you could talk about what's driving the growth there? I know advanced wearables have been strong in recent quarters. And if you could just give any update on new user growth?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Clifton Pemble
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 President, CEO & Director
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Yes. I think we saw growth across both kinds of products that we have in Fitness in terms of wearables that would be the running products as well as the advanced wellness products. And I would say that the registration behavior, the consumer behavior that we see on the registrations is very strong across the whole business, including all of our wearables in Outdoor and Fitness. The convincing majority of people coming to our platform are new users, and we're seeing strong double-digit growth in those registrations in new products year-over-year.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Joseph Nolan
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 Longbow Research LLC
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Okay. Great. And then fourth quarter promotions typically step up a little bit for the holiday season. Is it fair to expect a pretty comparable promotional environment compared to last year? Is there any puts and takes to think about within that?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Clifton Pemble
\f0\b0 \cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\i \cb2 President, CEO & Director
\f0\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 I would say that -- I would call it comparable. We have a lot of products to offer, which is great for retailers because there's something for everyone. And so we have strong promotions planned. I'd say they're in line with what we've seen in previous years, and I think we're really excited about what we have to offer.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \cb2 Operator
\f0\b0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 Your next question comes from the line of Ivan Feinseth with Tigress Financial Partners.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
